Use MAUI's `App` lifecycle events combined with `Preferences` for lightweight persistence:

**App.xaml.cs** — hook lifecycle events:
```csharp
public partial class App : Application
{
    public App()
    {
        InitializeComponent();
        MainPage = new NavigationPage(new NotePage());
    }

    protected override Window CreateWindow(IActivationState? activationState)
    {
        var window = base.CreateWindow(activationState);

        window.Deactivated += (s, e) =>
            WeakReferenceMessenger.Default.Send(new AppBackgroundMessage());

        window.Activated += (s, e) =>
            WeakReferenceMessenger.Default.Send(new AppForegroundMessage());

        return window;
    }
}
```

**Messages:**
```csharp
public sealed class AppBackgroundMessage { }
public sealed class AppForegroundMessage { }
```

**NotePage.xaml:**
```xml
<ContentPage xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui"
             xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2009/xaml"
             x:Class="MyApp.NotePage">
    <Editor x:Name="NoteEditor"
            Placeholder="Start typing your note..." />
</ContentPage>
```

**NotePage.xaml.cs** — save on background, restore on foreground:
```csharp
public partial class NotePage : ContentPage
{
    private const string DraftKey = "note_draft";

    public NotePage()
    {
        InitializeComponent();
        RestoreDraft();

        WeakReferenceMessenger.Default.Register<AppBackgroundMessage>(this, (r, m) =>
            SaveDraft());

        WeakReferenceMessenger.Default.Register<AppForegroundMessage>(this, (r, m) =>
            RestoreDraft());
    }

    private void SaveDraft()
    {
        Preferences.Set(DraftKey, NoteEditor.Text ?? string.Empty);
    }

    private void RestoreDraft()
    {
        NoteEditor.Text = Preferences.Get(DraftKey, string.Empty);
    }

    protected override void OnDisappearing()
    {
        base.OnDisappearing();
        WeakReferenceMessenger.Default.UnregisterAll(this);
    }
}
```

**Key points:**

- **`Window.Deactivated`/`Activated`** fire when the app backgrounds/foregrounds across all platforms.
- **`Preferences`** is fast, synchronous, and ideal for small strings like draft text. For larger data, use `SecureStorage` or file I/O.
- **`WeakReferenceMessenger`** (from `CommunityToolkit.Mvvm`) decouples `App` from your page. Install it via:
  ```
  dotnet add package CommunityToolkit.Mvvm
  ```
- Unregister in `OnDisappearing` to avoid leaks if the page is popped from the nav stack.
